<law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection amended="yes" chaptername="Cities Of The First Class" id="id00" statutenumber="16-218"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>16-218</statuteno><catchline id="id00">Officers; regulation.</catchline><para>Except as otherwise provided by law, a city of the first class by ordinance may regulate and prescribe the powers, duties, and compensation of the officers of the city and classify such offices, on the basis of merit as the city council shall provide for that purpose.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1901, c. 18, &#167; 48, XXIII, p. 250; </para><para>R.S.1913, &#167; 4834; </para><para>C.S.1922, &#167; 4002; </para><para>C.S.1929, &#167; 16-219; </para><para>Laws 1939, c. 11, &#167; 1, p. 78; </para><para>C.S.Supp.,1941, &#167; 16-219; </para><para>R.S.1943, &#167; 16-218; </para><para>Laws 2016, LB704, &#167; 24. </para></source></law>
